# {{ projectName }}

DARE-shaped MCP server (Python 3.11+). Default transport: **{{ defaultTransport }}**.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
python -m src.cli
```

## Commands

- `python -m src.cli` — start server (transport via --transport or MCP_TRANSPORT env)
- `pytest` — pytest suite
- `ruff check .` — lint
- `pip-audit` — dependency audit
- `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector python -m src.cli` — MCP Inspector

## Tools (registered in src/server.py via FastMCP)

| Name | Input | Output | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `echo` | `text: str` | `str` | Returns input verbatim. Smoke test. |

## Prompts

| Name | Args | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `summarize` | `text` | Summarize the input text. Placeholder. |

## Transports

Choose with `--transport stdio|sse|http` or `MCP_TRANSPORT`:

- `stdio` (default) — local agents. No port.
- `sse` — SSE-over-HTTP on `MCP_PORT` (default 3001).
- `http` — Streamable HTTP on `MCP_PORT` (default 3001).

## Architecture

- `src/server.py` — FastMCP instance, tools and prompts registered with @mcp.tool() / @mcp.prompt().
- `src/cli.py` — argparse entrypoint, transport dispatch.
- `src/transports/` — wrappers around mcp.run() calls for the 3 transports.
- `src/tools/`, `src/prompts/` — module per tool/prompt for organization.

## CLI inventory

`python -m src.cli --json --list-tools` returns the tool registry as JSON (M-03).

